rComments: Attending his lectures is kind of useless and he gives no feedback on anything. With that said, the course is literally a guaranteed A+ if you put in a little effort. You can tell he enjoys teaching and loves his students, but online teaching really is not his forte.

Really tranquil professor. You don't do much in class, but if you take the initiative to ask he will explain thoroughly. The course was very easy and definitely helped me understand some aspects of the accompanying course.

I believe he means well but does not know how to teach and didn't prepare. The class would consist of 2 presentations, and for the remaining hour he would go over elementary level grammar (to very intermediate 2nd year immersion students), how to write an essay, or how to answer a test question. Learned nothing, but easy A/A+ if you need the mark.

Most disorganized class I have ever taken in my entire life. Starts things, never finishes them. Doesn't have a clear order of teaching. Can't control a class. Super clueless. I absolutely despised this class. I learned absolutely nothing. Avoid this professor at all costs.
Very disorganized and no one felt prepared for the final.
Take this class and get an A+. Easiest grade booster of my life. Wish he taught more classes in upper years because I desperately need that A.
Worst FLS class in the world, I would rather have come back an extra year and get a different prof than have him!!

Do not take any course with this professor. He is incapable of communicating the required material and has no concept of how to teach university-level students. He does not foster an environment that helps with learning; rather, he arrogantly laughs at your mistakes. He does not explain his marking schemes. AVOID HIM. He will waste your money.
